world

Class SimpleSolid

  • java.lang.Object
    • world.SimpleObject
      • world.SimpleSolid
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    testObject

    public abstract class SimpleSolid
extends SimpleObject
    The basic colliding object. All collisions happen with a SimpleSolid. Furthermore, the SimpleSolid automatically sorts its z-index based off of the y-index on the screen.
    Since:
    1.2 Now all code is abstracted as MVC., 1.1
    Version:
    1.3 Fuzz movement was created.
    Author:
    Brian Nakayama

      • move

        public boolean move(int x,
           int y,
           boolean relative)
        The method for moving a SimpleSolid. Similar to SimpleObject.move(int, int, boolean), with the exception that it does not allow movements that overlap with another SimpleSolid's space. Furthermore, as of version 1.0 it does not attempt to move at all if encountering an overlap. The solids resort themselves when the y-axis has changed rows in the map.
        Overrides:
        move in class SimpleObject
        Parameters:
        x - The new x-coordinate.
        y - The new y-coordinate.
        relative - True to move relative from your position, else move absolutely.
        Returns:
        True iff the object moved successfully.

      • fuzzMove

        public boolean fuzzMove(int x,
               int y,
               int fuzz)
        The method for moving a solid, that will attempt to move when colliding on a corner (fuzz > 0) or will attempt to move as far along the direction indicated (fuzz = -1). Identical to move(int, int, boolean), except if there's a collision with only one object this method will move the object by the given fuzz amount in a favorable alignment so that this object is better situated to move when move is called again. Specifically, if we collide within cellWidth / 2 or cellHeight / 2 of a corner we move the object fuzz pixels towards the tip of the corner. This method always moves the object relative from its current position, and is not intended for large leaps greater than the size of the map cells.
        Parameters:
        x - The new relative x-coordinate.
        y - The new relative y-coordinate.
        fuzz - The alternative amount to move either NS or EW if there's a collision.
        Returns:
        True iff the intended move was made or the fuzz move.

      • approxMove

        public boolean approxMove(int x,
                 int y)
        The method for moving a solid, that will attempt to move as far along the direction indicated (Same as fuzzMove(int, int, int) where fuzz = -1). Specifically, it looks at the first object it has collided with (if a collision occurs), and it then moves the maximum amount in both the x and y directions without colliding.
        Parameters:
        x - The new relative x-coordinate.
        y - The new relative y-coordinate.
        Returns:
        True iff a normal move or the approximation move was made.
